wikipedia_page.main: Jack Price (birth unknown – death unknown) was an English professional rugby league footballer who played in the 1920s. He played at representative level for Great Britain and England, and at club level for Broughton Rangers and Wigan, as a second-row, or loose forward, i.e. number 11 or 12, or 13, during the era of contested scrums.
